JOHANNESBURG - IFP Leader, Mangosuthu Buthelezi has spoken fondly of struggle icon Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. He’s described her as a true leader, who suffered harshly under the apartheid regime. "I recall many occasions because both of them were fond of music. I remember many happy occasions when just the three of us were there. The woman, she could cook very salivating food which we enjoyed with Madiba," said Buthelezi. WATCH: ANC plans hive of activities to honour Winnie "I really recall with great emotions, those were happy occasion before both of them were persecuted by the apartheid regime. She was persecuted in hundred and one ways. It’s an important history of our country. I really loved her as a sister and one of my leaders,” he said. Memorial services are being held all over the country to honour Madikizela-Mandela. Madikizela-Mandela passed on a week ago and will be laid to rest on 14 April 2018.